{"TopicId":168305,"ForumId":20,"TopicTitle":"1.25 to 2.5 (and 2.5 to 3.75) cargo bays?","CreatedByName":"Phelan","CreatedById":160924,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-12-07T20:48:47Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Phelan","CreatedById":160924,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-12-07T20:48:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoes anyone know of any mods for cargo bays (or service bays or whatever) with the general shape of for example the Rockomax Brand Adapter (1.25 to 2.5 adapter) and Kerbodyne ADTP-2-3 (2.5 to 3.75)? Yes, I know I can clip stuff into the adapters, but that\u0027s always at best meh (especially if you want to access the stuff\u0027s right-click menus). Unstaged fairings won\u0027t help since I want to attach stuff to the sides (think of a SpaceX Dragon-like cargo capsule for example).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"regex","CreatedById":70807,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-12-07T22:36:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSXT has some round cargo bays, IIRC.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed3015059439\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/151129-131-sxt-continued/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:208px;max-width:500px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Phelan","CreatedById":160924,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-12-07T23:00:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI know, but I really mean bays with a node on top (for docking ports or parachutes and such).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JadeOfMaar","CreatedById":167617,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-12-07T23:31:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAsking for \u0022adapter cargo bays\u0022? Interesting. From what I know, a cargo bay\u0027s effective space (for aero shielding) can only have a cylinder shape, not a conical or any other shape. Such a bay may have to be provided in 2\u002B component parts to allow for stacking effective spaces with differing radii, and to keep the practicality of attaching things to the inside of the wall at the wider or widest end.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sebi.zzr","CreatedById":81294,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-12-07T23:40:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223238107\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022168305\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221512687653\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022160924\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Phelan\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n37 minutes ago, Phelan said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI know, but I really mean bays with a node on top (for docking ports or parachutes and such).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSoon:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022kH4kpKL.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022307\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/kH4kpKL.png\u0022 style=\u0022width:476px;\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFrom:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed3494527448\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/163824-ksp-weekly%C2%A0the-9th-planet/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:214px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Phelan","CreatedById":160924,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-12-07T23:47:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks, but that looks basically like a specialized fairing. For one, it\u0027s too small for my purposes, it doesn\u0027t look like anything could be attached to the outsides (like SpaceX-style SuperDraco engines from the Kerbal Reusability mod), and it doesn\u0027t open and close like a cargo or service bay.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"hraban","CreatedById":145453,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-12-08T11:17:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan lang=\u0022en\u0022 xml:lang=\u0022en\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan\u003ENot exactly what you are looking for, but maybe the right way?\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cimg class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022768\u0022 src=\u0022http://www.hraban.de/storage/cache/images/000/220/DLMS-C,medium_large.2x.1497642583.png\u0022 style=\u0022width:300px;height:auto;\u0022 width=\u0022757\u0022 alt=\u0022DLMS-C,medium_large.2x.1497642583.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Phelan","CreatedById":160924,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-12-08T11:21:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot ideal, but as far as I can tell from the pic, it\u0027d be a start \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E Where did you stumble over it?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nightside","CreatedById":150244,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-12-08T11:32:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223238393\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022168305\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221512732105\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022160924\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Phelan\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 minutes ago, Phelan said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot ideal, but as far as I can tell from the pic, it\u0027d be a start \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E Where did you stumble over it?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/160924-phelan/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022160924\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/160924-phelan/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Phelan\u003C/a\u003E, he made it! Check the link in his sig.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Phelan","CreatedById":160924,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-12-08T11:37:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAh, okay, I had actually looked at the mod at some point already, but hadn\u0027t tried it out. Gonna do that then \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbalfreak","CreatedById":181766,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-12-10T14:20:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think Mk2 expansion has one for Mk2 to 1.25. Not exacly what you are searching, but maybe could be useful.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Phelan","CreatedById":160924,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-12-10T14:47:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo, I\u0027m already playing with M2 expansion, no \u0027adapter\u0027 cargobays, only structural ones (hollow, without fuel).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbalfreak","CreatedById":181766,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-12-10T15:34:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223240251\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022168305\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221512917265\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022160924\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Phelan\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Phelan said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo, I\u0027m already playing with M2 expansion, no \u0027adapter\u0027 cargobays, only structural ones (hollow, without fuel).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSorry, it\u0027s from SXT. Here\u0027s a pic:\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022bP9YKhV.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022557\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/bP9YKhV.png\u0022 width=\u0022679\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Phelan","CreatedById":160924,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-12-10T15:38:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAhhhh, yes, that looks about perfect, thank you \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTime to install it \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbalfreak","CreatedById":181766,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-12-10T16:21:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you are not familiar with\u00A0mods, here\u0027s two suggestions:\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nSXT has a LOT of parts, some you maybe find useful, others don\u0027t. A mod called Janitor\u0027s Closet\u00A0can disable parts that you don\u0027t want, since they consume RAM, load time and space in the list. But you\u0027ll probably find more cool and useful parts that you\u0027ll want to keep.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nYou can also use this with a\u00A0Mk2 \u0026gt; 2.5 adapter, and make it 3.75\u00A0with Tweakscale.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nAnother very great but less known\u00A0mod for Mk2 parts:\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/145635-131-quiztech-aero-pack-continued/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003Ehttps://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/145635-131-quiztech-aero-pack-continued/\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Phelan","CreatedById":160924,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-12-10T16:25:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlready got Janitor\u0027s Closet, but yup, thanks \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd I\u0027m ideally just looking for \u0027round\u0027 ones (main interest is realyl basically an unmanned \u0027cargo\u0027 2.5m pod \u00E0 la Dragon. Besides, trying to get on without Tweakscale this time around, it can be a bit cheaty, at least the cost (scaling down bigger parts can make them EXTREMELY cheap \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:wink:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E )\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Phelan","CreatedById":160924,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-12-10T20:14:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDammit, didn\u0027t see in the pic that it was a Mk2 adapter, I should have looked more closely \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:(\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_sad.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:(\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt \u003Cem\u003Eseems\u003C/em\u003E that shaped cargo bays shouldn\u0027t be an issue with the aerodynamics of KSP, so I guess I\u0027ll just keep hoping for some \u0027round\u0027 adapter ones \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:/\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/ZNGIcon1.png\u0022 title=\u0022:/\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}